<h1 id="s13">11. Setup, Commands, Inputs &amp; Outputs</h1>
<p><b>Prerequisites:</b> Node.js 18+, npm, an Anthropic API key, a browser.</p>
<p><b>Setup &amp; run:</b></p>
<ol>
<li><code>npm install</code></li>
<li>Copy <code>.env.example</code> to <code>.env</code>; set <code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code>.</li>
<li><code>npm start</code> &rarr; open <code>http://localhost:3000</code>.</li>
<li>Upload a PDF/DOCX contract &rarr; <b>Upload Contract</b>; open it from <b>View Analysis History</b>.</li>
</ol>
<p><b>Inputs:</b> one PDF/DOCX (&le;25 MB, machine-readable text). <b>Outputs:</b> a self-contained HTML dashboard (saved to <code>output/</code> and history), a PII-masked <code>output/audit.log</code>, a per-run log file in <code>output/logs/</code> (one per analyze click), and a deterministic <code>cache/</code> entry. Full details in <code>README.md</code>.</p>
