<small>Prefer a live demo (bonus points); keep the recording as backup.</small></div>

<h1 id="s15">13. Safety &amp; Compliance Note</h1>
<p><b>No real PHI/PII.</b> Only synthetic sample contracts are used; uploaded files are deleted immediately after processing; logs and the audit trail are PII-masked (emails, phones, PAN, Aadhaar, SSN, MRN, keys, passwords).</p>
<p><b>PHI screening (above and beyond).</b> The tool analyzes contracts, not patient records. Every upload is screened for patient identifiers — MRN, date of birth, SSN, ICD codes, health-insurance claim/beneficiary IDs, and NPI; any hit is flagged in the audit log (<code>phi_flagged</code>), raised as a run warning, and noted in the dashboard's Limitations legend, so no real PHI can slip in unnoticed.</p>
<p><b>Responsible-AI safeguards.</b> Grounded extraction (no fabrication; "Not stated" for missing data), evidence + confidence per finding, injection/jailbreak defense, output validation, and deterministic re-computation of critical facts.</p>
<p><b>Human-in-the-loop.</b> The dashboard is a decision-support aid, not legal advice; it recommends but never auto-executes; referenced-but-unuploaded agreements are flagged for manual validation.</p>
<table>
<tr><th style="width:40%">Risk</th><th>Mitigation</th></tr>
<tr><td>AI misreads / misses a clause</td><td>Evidence + confidence per row; human review; "first-pass aid" framing</td></tr>
<tr><td>Different results across runs</td><td>Temperature 0 + deterministic cache</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fabricated money</td><td>Nulled when not stated; value-at-risk labelled directional</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hidden instructions in a contract</td><td>Untrusted-data framing + injection screening + system-prompt protection</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sensitive data in logs</td><td>PII masking everywhere</td></tr>
<tr><td>Inconsistent EM/pricing</td><td>Deterministically reconciled (EM trusted, pricing corrected)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Referenced agreement not provided</td><td>Flagged for manual validation, not assumed</td></tr>
</table>

<h1 id="s16">14. Final Pre-Submit Checklist</h1>
<p class="chk">
&#9744; Run the agent once from a clean environment (fresh install, valid key).<br>
&#9744; Verify the generated artifact (values correct; "Not stated" where missing).<br>
&#9744; Remove any confidential data; confirm samples are synthetic; ensure <code>.env</code> is not included.<br>
&#9744; Confirm the README steps reproduce the result independently.<br>
&#9744; Include the DoD-to-evidence mapping (Section 5).<br>
&#9744; Capture output artifacts (screenshots + <code>audit.log</code>) and the demo (link/file).
</p>

<h1 id="s17">15. Submission Readiness Checklist</h1>
<p class="chk">
<b>Build &amp; run</b><br>
&#9744; <code>npm install</code> succeeds &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; <code>.env</code> has a valid key &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; <code>npm start</code> serves the app<br>
&#9744; Upload a PDF and a DOCX — both analyze successfully<br>
&#9744; EM &amp; pricing are consistent; page numbers match clauses; counts match the ledger<br>
<b>Evidence</b><br>
&#9744; Screenshots pasted in Section 8 &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; <code>audit.log</code> copied to <code>Submission/output-artifacts/</code><br>
&#9744; Demo recorded / rehearsed &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; Sample contracts in <code>Submission/sample-data/</code> (synthetic)<br>
<b>Docs</b><br>
&#9744; README complete &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; DoD evidence (Section 5) &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; Compliance note (Section 13)<br>
<b>Package</b><br>
&#9744; Team details filled at top &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; ZIP excludes <code>.env</code>, <code>node_modules/</code>, <code>output/</code>, <code>cache/</code><br>
&#9744; "Built with Claude Code" stated &nbsp;&nbsp; &#9744; Submitted before the deadline
</p>

<h1 id="s18">16. Appendix — Configuration, Glossary &amp; File Inventory</h1>
<h2>16.1 Configuration (environment variables)</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Setting</th><th>Default</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td><code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code></td><td>—</td><td>AI service key (in <code>.env</code>, never committed)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>ANTHROPIC_MODEL</code></td><td>claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929</td><td>Model used</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>PORT</code></td><td>3000</td><td>Web server port</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>MAX_TOKENS</code></td><td>16000</td><td>Output tokens per request (auto-continues)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>RATE_MAX</code> / <code>RATE_WINDOW_MS</code></td><td>20 / 60000</td><td>Rate limit</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>PRICE_PER_MTOK_IN</code> / <code>_OUT</code></td><td>3 / 15</td><td>Cost-estimate rates (USD per 1M tokens)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>DISABLE_CACHE</code></td><td>0</td><td>Set 1 to force a fresh model call</td></tr>
</table>
<h2>16.2 Glossary</h2>
<p><b>SLA</b> — service-level agreement. <b>EM Level</b> — engagement/delivery model (EM 1 Staff Aug … EM 4 Fixed Price/Output+/Outcome+). <b>Priority (P1–P4)</b> — urgency. <b>Value at Risk</b> — directional money exposure. <b>Grounding</b> — using only the source document. <b>Hallucination</b> — unsupported AI output. <b>Prompt injection</b> — hidden instructions in input. <b>Temperature</b> — AI randomness (0 = most repeatable).</p>
<h2>16.3 File inventory</h2>
<p><code>index.html</code>, <code>analysis-history.html</code>, <code>server.js</code>, <code>extract.js</code>, <code>analyze.js</code>, <code>guardrails.js</code>, <code>buildHtml.js</code>, <code>dashboard-template.html</code>, <code>analysis-prompt.txt</code>, <code>package.json</code>, <code>.env.example</code>, <code>.gitignore</code>, <code>README.md</code>, and the <code>Submission/</code> pack (index, DoD evidence, compliance note, demo script, sample data, output artifacts).</p>

<p style="margin-top:20pt;color:#888;font-style:italic">End of document. Replace all orange placeholders before submitting.</p>

